We recommended that Management:
a. Direct the OIC – Municipal Treasurer to prepare statement of accounts for the Lessees, and require to pay the corresponding unpaid monthly rentals and penalty/ies before any renewal of the contract in their favor;
b. Require the OIC-Municipal Treasurer to maintain complete and updated Subsidiary Ledgers of rental income of the occupants;
c. Require the OIC-Municipal Treasurer to monitor strictly the collection of market rentals; and
d. Strictly enforce compliance with the terms and conditions stipulated in the Lease contract.
